commit_message:
Remove the urlquote to arguments passed to reverse

In the container dashboard, I removed the urlquote to all
arguments passed to the reverse function since the reverse
function runs the urlquote on the arguments.

Change-Id: I4186ded9a2f52b6e56a12e8c521cb33fb3633a48
Closes-Bug: 1347734
Co-Authored-By: Masco Kaliyamoorthy <Masco.kaliyamoorthy@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Do not run git-cloned ksc master tests when local client specified

There is no reason to run both the KSC Master test and a locally
specified keystoneclient. If the local keystoneclient path is set
only use the KcOptTestCase not the KcMasterTestCase.

Change-Id: Ib9a1e06b2e760a97e3318263b85631c436e23141
Closes-bug: #1371428

commit_message:
Don't use __add__ with oslo.i18n Message object

This change fixes the automated generation of the config-reference
tables using the autohelp script from openstack-doc-tools.

Closes-Bug: #1349567
Change-Id: I7a0b1ce3d15ed2d0e09bea18b258156d934b6dee

commit_message:
[HBase] Catch AlreadyExists error in Connection upgrade

Now in upstream, if HBase table exists when we upgrade
backend AlreadyExists exception is raised. Also
exception raising interrupts creating of other tables.
It is an incorrect behavior because we should create
all tables and migrate them if need or use existing
tables.

Change-Id: I8e8a8ae633351de8393b5103910510dd635245be
Closes: bug #1370508

commit_message:
Fix Broken links in devref/filter_scheduler.rst

There were broken links on the following class
'AggregateNumInstancesFilter', 'RamWeigher' in
document filter_scheduler.html. Fix these broken
links.

Change-Id: I3cac48a6ad466a32a88c23c9f128e66dae5889ee
Closes-Bug: #1363955

commit_message:
fix EC2 Signature Version 4 calculation, in the case of POST

When calculating the AWS Signature Version 4, in the case of POST,
We need to set the CanonicalQueryString to an empty string. this
follows the implementation of the AWS and boto clients.

Change-Id: Iad4e392119067e246c7b77009da3fef48d251382
Closes-Bug: 1360892

commit_message:
check the block_device_allocate_retries

we need to check the value of the configuration item
block_device_allocate_retries in order to ensure to
retry at least once,done like that configuration
item network_allocate_retries

Change-Id: Ia5b65bd160cb4e740d21c1b51d234e14e33135e7
Closes-Bug:#1363558

commit_message:
Improve iptables_manager _modify_rules() method

As the number of ports per default security group increases, the
number of iptables entries on the Compute Node grows.  Because of
this, there is a gradual increase in the time taken to apply chains
and rules.

Currently we are using list comprehensions to find if a new chain or
rule matches an existing one.  Instead, walk through the list in
reverse to find a matching entry.

Added a new method, _find_last_entry(), to return the entry we are
searching for.

Change-Id: I3585479ffa00be556b8b21dc9dbd6b36ad37f4de
Closes-Bug: #1302272
Related-Bug: #1253993
(cherry picked from commit 0c202ab3e453e38c09f04978e4fce30d6ee6350c)

commit_message:
Add multinic API unit test

Multinic api unit test is not sufficient, so this patch
adds a testcase for removing a fixed IP when the IP is not
found.

Change-Id: Ice04806269a92244bd068b90e9934eaedb17a1b4

commit_message:
labs: remove redundant restart for ovs agent

Setup_neutron_network.sh restarts neutron-plugin-openvswitch-agent twice.
The second instance does not seem necessary and is not documented in
the install-guide, either.

Change-Id: I0cd1d64c94fd64130c530e761879515b9368c7b4

commit_message:
Adds EPEL repo, cleans up rhel7 repos

This patch adds a new EPEL element for use with EL-based distros
in accordance with the official docs[1].  This patch also
modifies the rhel7 element to not use the hard-coded repo file.

[1] https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/EPEL

Change-Id: Ib2fa24b2d519837271a0e213a2dc5a012cc31f3c

i have two concerns:

- it's the almost worst time to perform sweeps like this because it would interfere other reviews.  please consider postponing to eg. early in Kilo.
- @author can be considered as a part of copyright notice.  in that case, it isn't a good idea to modify them mechanically."}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2014-08-06 19:45:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Good change, btu this is going to cause a lot of rebases, which wipe out review progress.  Given the trouble getting review attention, and the fast approaching Juno-3 deadline, I also think this should wait.  I see several conflicts in the lbaas code we're working on alone, and we can't be alone in that."}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2014-08-06 19:45:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2014-08-07 05:23:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

@Doug and Yamampto - I do not think that this will cause any problems with rebases. This is something that we need to add to be in line with all other projects. Due to the fact that a hacking rule is added all new code added that has 'Author' will fail at the gate.
Please reconsider"}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2014-08-07 06:26:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I saw several files in this change that the lbaas team has refactored heavily, and I know we removed @author at the same time, which I think will end up as a merge conflict.  And given how hard it's been getting core reviewer time, for our 7 dependent reviews chain, wiping out any +2's in there for a mechanical change would make me weep.  :-)

I'll try a cherry-pick merge on top tomorrow and remove my -1 if it's clean.  Either way, I'm in favor of the change.  I know that a bunch of other hacking fixes were made a month or two ago, and they're all approved but waiting for churn reasons.  We could try to coordinate this one with mestery to have it go in at the same time as those..."}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2014-08-07 08:42:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I think that we should make an effort to imporve our code, and if this is about a rebase then that should be ok. If you want I can base this on top of the LB changes.
But a core should take into account rebases...'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2014-08-08 02:43:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Code-Review'}, {'account_id': 6854, 'date': '2014-08-08 03:27:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Gary,

what's wrong with doing this later?"}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2014-08-08 05:21:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Yamamoto - I do not see any reason why we should not do this now. Lets strive to have automatic checks remove things like this. It will make the code be on par with nova, oslo etc.
I do not see any reason why we should prevent something like this - it only improves things'}, {'account_id': 6854, 'date': '2014-08-08 12:21:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

garyk,

another potential need of rebase at this point is severe.
i understand you have a different opinion.
i agree that core should take account of rebases but
they seem already overloaded in reality.'}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2014-08-10 06:51:04.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-10 06:51:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I am a fan of this change. I still think it is a good time to do this even though there are the topics already discussed in the past comments. We have more than a week for the feature proposed freeze (Aug 21). Even though this change may require extra rebases for other proposed changes, most patches are required to change their code to address comments themselves and the only exception is a case where a merge conflict on a final merge. Thus I think it is not a big thing.

Copyright (C) 2014 Fumihiko Kakuma <kakuma at valinux co jp>'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-19 08:42:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

@fumihiko, authorship attribution is handled by git itself.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-19 08:43:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

That said, have we asked legal first whether it's ok to remove those lines like that?"}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-08-19 09:12:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

afaik there has never been a policy of autorship attribution using @author tags.
This is all that I could find: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LegalIssuesFAQ#Copyright_Headers

I don't think the @author tags or "Author" lines were ever meant to have any validity regarding copyright or recognition for authors. There are some of these tags on modules which have been authored hundreds of times.

also, I seem to recall the ASF has mandated for removal of these tags as well. We use apache licenses but then I'm not sure also we comply with ASF decisions.

However, I also don't see why if we remove an @author tag we should then give copyright to the person which was in the author tag. I might be missing something legally sensible but that seems silly to me.'}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-08-19 09:13:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-19 09:22:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Ihar, I know that. I thought that it is rule of OpenStack.

commit_message:
Remove @author(s) from copyright statements

We have git to track authorship, so let's not pad source files
with it as well.

A hacking check has been added for this. The value is N322.

Change-Id: Iab0b64d417e0bb41a6b455e2ac377deee64ec3ee

commit_message:
Honour validly tagged versions.

There was a bug in the code to ignore bad tags - we stopped outputting
actual release versions altogether.

Change-Id: I0eb3fe6a09f0e696b96eab1e14549ea0a8fe27ba
Closes-Bug: #1370608

commit_message:
Only run worldump.py if it is there

Check for worldump being present and executable before trying to run
it. Otherwise an error can happen that masks the error that caused
an early exit.

worlddump.py will not be present if the target devstack directory
is not yet there (has not been git cloned yet). Generally speaking
this will only happen when making (and testing) changes to grenade
itself or when something has gone very wrong quite early in a grenade
run.

The target release directory is used because at the current time
worldump.py is present in Juno but not in Icehouse.

Change-Id: I974f5bea23464b4143db8b2d35927d5350921bd2

commit_message:
Add Core, Ram and Disk filter to fake virt setting

The FakeVirt driver shouldn't need custom scheduling options, so it run
instead of a real virt driver for testing purposes. This simplifies the
use case where someone wants to run the FakeVirt driver along side a
real driver so someone can test there cloud application without wasting
real instances.

Since the FakeVirt driver should look like it has near infinite resources,
turn on Core, Ram and Disk filters to make sure the drive works with them
enabled.

Change-Id: Ic7ec87e4d497d9db58eec93f2b304fe9770a2bbc
Related-Bug: #1268943

commit_message:
Install MySQL-python for keystone with rpm system

MySQL-python is needed for keystone and we were installing it
implicitely only for apts and not for rpms. Fix keystone only devstack
install on a pristine vm.

Change-Id: I0d117513af4e2ad58635f7a7b22f7a6e3ff36a38

does this have an effect on memory?  isn't this really *increasing* memory usage, the opposite of what that flag was supposed to do?"}, {'account_id': 7175, 'date': '2014-09-15 14:47:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-15 14:51:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Yes, this will allow keystone to use more memory. Also, other servers might use more memory too since the stack won't be waiting for keystone all the time. Maybe the change to set API_WORKERS on the other servers will have such a dramatic effect on memory usage that there's some freed up for keystone now, and we can all get our test results faster."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2014-09-18 14:10:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

We had a product team internally point this out to us in Icehouse and bumping up the api_workers increased their throughput by 20%, so we started setting it to nproc in our internal Tempest runs also.  So far so good.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2014-09-18 14:49:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122013/ is going to always set API_WORKERS to a default value, the [ -n $API_WORKERS ] test can be removed.'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-18 15:04:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

Marking WIP. Got a comment from dtroyer to handle. Also, latest discussion was that keystone should default to #cpu workers and ignore this option.'}, {'account_id': 2903, 'date': '2014-09-18 18:42:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Based on conversations in -QA in IRC the admin_workers should be based on API_WORKERS and the public workers should be their own separate knob. This is because the public workers pose a bigger bottleneck and likely should actually be n-cpu not max(n-cpu / 2, 2) [or other math]'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-19 01:21:02.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-19 04:22:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Configurable Keystone admin workers

The API_WORKERS option wasn't setting the number of admin workers
for the Keystone server when running in eventlet mode. This will
allow for control of throughput and memory usage.

Change-Id: Iecbce4a601f93784164e53d8b0c542d48f7b5650

commit_message:
Change "is lazy loaded" detection method in db_api test

This changes the test_security_group_get_no_instances() method to use a simpler
method of determining if instances is loaded on a security_group after a get
operation.

Change-Id: Ifea6c20bcaa201167ef5679f3ddb9ae8141bbbf5
Closes-Bug: #1349147

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-19 07:57:11.000000000', 'message': 'Fix "rally info" failure in case of empty docstrings

In case the input query for "rally info find ... " requested for a benchmark
scenario with an empty docstring, the CLI failed with an exception. Instead,
we should print that there is no info about that scenario.

Change-Id: If3a806f794f9b11ce1eb44eaabce732183c4c99b
Closes-Bug: 1371461
'}]
commit_message:
Fix "rally info" failure in case of empty docstrings

In case the input query for "rally info find ... " requested for a benchmark
scenario with an empty docstring, the CLI failed with an exception. Instead,
we should print that there is no info about that scenario.

Change-Id: If3a806f794f9b11ce1eb44eaabce732183c4c99b
Closes-Bug: 1371461

commit_message:
libvirt: convert test_vif.py to avoid DB usage

Remove use of the flavour APIs in the VIF test case avoiding
the need to hit the database. This allows conversion to the
NoDBTestCase which speeds up execution from 3 seconds to 0.3
seconds.

Partial-bug: #1369516
Change-Id: Ib0239b0f943baa1b1d81478b3b0d1e2ce1fb8722

commit_message:
libvirt: remove pointless class in util test suite

The test_utils.py module had two separate test classes defined
for no real benefit. This is left over from merging tests from
two separate files together.

Change-Id: I808719955f90f7333aecbb9f3a1e19a377553edf

commit_message:
Remove the dependency on prettytable

Instead of pulling in yet another dependency for a mostly
debugging feature lets just have a tiny table object/class
that can work fine for our usage instead.

Part of blueprint top-level-types

Fixes bug 1368975

Change-Id: I21b1bd8152e5bf64b9060d3aabf4384350d05c0f

commit_message:
BSN: Add context to backend request for debugging

Include the request context with calls to the backend
Big Switch controllers to assist with event correlation
and debugging object provenance. The auth token is
stripped since this information is sensitive and
these requests will appear in debug logs.

This also removes mutable objects from default arguments
in some of the server manager function definitions that
were interferring with the new use of the headers dict.

Closes-Bug: #1364696
Change-Id: I5b80b1596cc145742457b3603cbcd67f6e0d9f36

commit_message:
Increase the 3PAR hostname length

The latest 3PAR firmware supports a hostname of 31 characters.
This patch increases the hostname on the 3PAR from 23 characters to
31.

The driver currently has a fallback mechanism in place for detecting
existing hosts.   This handles the case where upgrading from
Icehouse to Juno where Icehouse hosts have a limit of 23 characters.

Change-Id: I171e54b2e03a4ae11d2bf07c9c48febab268ce84
Closes-Bug: 1371242

commit_message:
Make Swift uses API_WORKERS

Keep the default to 1 instead of going wild, cause Swift really would
kill the VM if we let it go (and keeps the old behavior).

Change-Id: I7449c1bb485459169b8870c871b887cbab8be865

[{'created': '2014-09-19 00:07:02.000000000', 'message': "Test for unicode names in AccountBroker.merge_items()

ContainerBroker.merge_items() had a bug in it where non-ASCII Unicode
names would possibly result in duplicate entries in container
databases. AccountBroker.merge_items() doesn't do the same
bulk-operations tricks that ContainerBroker does, so it doesn't
currently have the bug. This commit just adds a test to ensure the bug
doesn't creep in should someone decide to make AccountBroker look more
like ContainerBroker someday.

Change-Id: Id2ac129828dbdf55b609d839ce4d9d42437ee0a3
"}]
commit_message:
Test for unicode names in AccountBroker.merge_items()

ContainerBroker.merge_items() had a bug in it where non-ASCII Unicode
names would possibly result in duplicate entries in container
databases. AccountBroker.merge_items() doesn't do the same
bulk-operations tricks that ContainerBroker does, so it doesn't
currently have the bug. This commit just adds a test to ensure the bug
doesn't creep in should someone decide to make AccountBroker look more
like ContainerBroker someday.

Change-Id: Id2ac129828dbdf55b609d839ce4d9d42437ee0a3

commit_message:
Make cli test namespace include test files

This commit adds the missing init files from the cli test suite. When
the test files were moved into subdirs as part of change
82e667ef4eaa79c20bbb7a528abda358edfb6a83 init files weren't included.
This meant that discovery couldn't find the tests and they weren't
runnable. Also, by enabling the tests unfixed paths also neede to be
updated in the heat tests, because they were referring to the
incorrect location.

Change-Id: I5807bb2f1f70cb0747c7831425e5df2bc48dd6ed

commit_message:
Have examples run in the py27 environment and make them work

It is great to ensure that the examples that tooz has actually run
during testing time, so enable this as well as adjust the examples
to create unique group ids and run for a limited amount of time instead
of running forever (and fix a few other brokeness)...

Change-Id: I573cf5946a1d3f13862c0c28cf3a5d7fc6178873

commit_message:
correct _sync_instance_power_state log message

As reported by a user: the src and dest hosts listed were actually in
reverse order, making this log message quite confusing to
operators. Flipped to the correct requested order.

Change-Id: If9b31bceb56b66af70cddb88dbece7a180e4c2c8
Closes-Bug: #1370885

Adds taskmanager_manager = trove.taskmanager.manager.Manager

- User reports this is needed for apt-based installs; so adding it to all
even if distro has this correct

commit_message:
Make rescheduling of l3 agent more resilient

In order to make l3 agent restart more resilient
and idempotent do:

1) delete agent after resource is stopped and
all the stuff is cleaned up

2) reschedule not only dead routers/networks but also
orphaned routers/networks

3) enclose get_pid_list_for_ns_list function argument
in cleanup function into double quoutes
or it will use only the first argument
and will not work with several networks

Change-Id: I06a89f0015c8f188d212995ed0652c5ee2cc1c47
Related-Bug: #1371550

commit_message:
Don't elevate context when rescheduling

The rescheduled launch should be executed with the same context
as the original request, so make sure that we aren't passing an
elevated context to reschedule.

Change-Id: Ic528f10067fa2977cc375c41b9c65d3517524ff8
Resolves-bug: 1366181

commit_message:
Framework for resource safe class level fixtures

Modify BaseTestCase, add resource_setup and resource_cleanup
methods, invoked by setUpClass and tearDownClass respectively.

Partially-implements bp:resource-cleanup

Change-Id: I5f025b4f76d6d85fbefbada9475daf784425037a

With Fixture objects and test cases it is important to upcall first
rather than later to allow base classes to configure their internal
test tracking state. Failing to do so allows bugs like this one to
occur - when failure occurs early, the state required to gather
environmental details about the failure is not prepared, and the
test machinery will raise secondary exceptions as it tries to do that.
This may even obscure the original error.

I've taken a fairly minimal approach here - I think it would be
possible and likely even desirable to get rid of the test classes
altogether - this module appears to have very little, if any, actual
test code - its all glue for managing the test database connections.
However I know zzzeek is working on a fairly large reorg in this
area and I don't want to conceptually clash with that - we can do
further cleanups later.

Co-Authored-By: Robert Collins <rbtcollins@hp.com>

commit_message:
Fixup Fixtures Use in db test classes.

With Fixture objects and test cases it is important to upcall first
rather than later to allow base classes to configure their internal
test tracking state. Failing to do so allows bugs like this one to
occur - when failure occurs early, the state required to gather
environmental details about the failure is not prepared, and the
test machinery will raise secondary exceptions as it tries to do that.
This may even obscure the original error.

I've taken a fairly minimal approach here - I think it would be
possible and likely even desirable to get rid of the test classes
altogether - this module appears to have very little, if any, actual
test code - its all glue for managing the test database connections.
However I know zzzeek is working on a fairly large reorg in this
area and I don't want to conceptually clash with that - we can do
further cleanups later.

Co-Authored-By: Robert Collins <rbtcollins@hp.com>

Change-Id: Ic9f24aa2352d097a10be8420b701fa9f588b21b0
Closes-Bug: #1330763

commit_message:
Made Admin State choice more human readable

The Admin State choices in create forms throughout horizon
were not very clear, this patch presents that choice in a much more
readable and understandable way. The field is changed from a boolean
field to a choice field with the different states, making it more
obvious what is being decided.

Change-Id: I7091e5ccf91c57d3f64e2d4415bed952d09ada71
Closes-Bug: 1370322

commit_message:
Enforce required config params for ODL driver

Raise a config error during initialization if
there is no URL, username, or password specified
in the config for the OpenDayLight ML2 driver.

Closes-Bug: #1301432
Change-Id: I65fc94d3eaaade3d1402d1c82d2c1edfa7133d5a

Update cinder.conf.sample

Whether we should be checking this in the gate or not for
stable inparticular is a whole seperate argument.

commit_message:
Add delete operations for the ODL MechanismDriver

This commit adds delete operations (networks, subnets and ports) for the ODL MechanismDriver.
It also modifies sync_single_resource to reduce db operations.

Change-Id: I03ca04c83ac2ef9c879fbd87e74bae495daea16d
Closes-Bug: #1324450
Partial-Bug: #1325184

commit_message:
Fix docstring for disk_cachemodes

The docstring for the disk_cachemodes option implied a syntax that is
incorrect for a ListOpt.  Change the example to match exactly what you
would put in the config file for it to work.

Change-Id: Ie999d2799dba6c47facdc771e1cf6081d28d6b85
Closes-Bug: #1106423
(cherry picked from commit 1df9b26b51ff3a153b93d79e25bef454e08a8e38)

commit_message:
Add declaration of 'refresh_instance_security_rules' to virt driver

The method 'refresh_instance_security_rules' was not defined
in the virt driver ComputeDriver class. In cases where the
underlying virt driver does not support security groups
an exception would be encountered indication that the driver
class does not have the specific attribute.

In addition to adding the method the patch set also catches the
exception NotImplementedError and logs a warning.

Closes-bug: #1269448
(cherry picked from commit 5a98d7b61fa6adb1557e69f2f234406be0e2739c)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/virt/hyperv/test_hypervapi.py

Change-Id: Ia36b0dfb54a3ede86467d87f0650a0902adb6d46

commit_message:
Update the state graph builder to use state machine type

To build the state diagrams switch from using a custom
algorithm that builds a state machine in a table to using
our state machine class to build those same machines before
translation into a dot diagram.

This also allows us to use the state machine that already
is being used in the action engine as the source of transitions
to build the dot diagram with.

Change-Id: I4a0d16a3fb7c620c2774b535ab952b5d5006e9e9

commit_message:
Expand documention on failures and wrapped failures types

To make it more clear why these objects and types exist and when
and why they are used and reraised increase the verbosity of the
comments and associated inline documentation on these two classes
to help explain there existence & usefulness.

Change-Id: I742bbcd69c71df80e6de7becc8aee153bf16b34b

commit_message:
Make output from check_logs less verbose

This commit changes the output of check_logs.py to be a bit more
concise and clear. Instead of printing out every instance of errors
found in the log files it will only print out which individual files
had errors. If a file is marked as not allowing ERRORS or TRACES it
also prints that along with the filename. This should hopefully avoid
confusion around the operation of this script running in the gate.

Change-Id: Ib2a9a9736470cd3b445fb51a95a1a6c6696bb2cc

commit_message:
Ability to add form confirm/cancel button labels

We repeat a lot of templating code in our forms. It makes sense to abstract
some of these repetitive logic and reduce the clutter. This is an unintrusive
patch aim to give users ability to specify confirm and cancel labels in the
form class.

Change-Id: I6eba93c61a3a6a94ac7b42f199bfb95df86e96b6
Partially-Implements: blueprint form-template-to-view

commit_message:
Make cells 'flavorid' for resizes

Cells should use 'flavorid' (not 'id') for resizes.

bug 1241222

Change-Id: I57b997425f183f25d3ca032c7d8c35c1f49e3afc
(cherry picked from commit 034df6e875d6c0b590f3cfb802574c2f982fd534)
